BFN 

  [Text] Beijing, June 23 (XINHUA) -- Chinese Vice-Premier Li 
Lanqing met here today with Wayne Booker, executive 
vice-president of Ford International automotive operations of 
the United States. 
  Li spoke highly of the cooperation between Ford and the 
Chinese side, and said that there was great potential in China's 
auto industry. 
  Booker and his party arrived here today at the invitation of 
the Ministry of Machinery Industry of China. 
  During their stay in China, they will discuss cooperation in 
manufacturing auto components with relevant departments of China. 

